---
description: Engine code rules
globs: ["src/engine/**"]
---
- No content IDs, no game-specific logic. If you're writing "if (itemId === ...)" stop
  and use a tag, a def field, or a registered behavior instead.
- Every new def type needs: a Zod schema in src/engine/schemas/, ContentRegistry
  support, and a section in docs/ADDING_CONTENT.md.
- New component types must be registered in EntityFactory's component map.
- Pure logic (stats math, crafting checks, loot rolls) gets a Vitest unit test in tests/.
- Emit events for anything another system might care about. Emitting is cheap.
- Phaser objects never leak into pure-logic modules (stats/, CraftingSystem core).
